      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "OBAT Helpers excels in operational transparency and accountability, earning an <cite id=\"16\">overall score of 90.90.33333333333333/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. This includes perfect <cite id=\"17\">100/100 scores in both Culture & Accountability and Leadership & Adaptability</cite> beacons. Their impact is quantifiable through the maintenance of <cite id=\"18\">14 distinct outcome metrics</cite> tracked via Candid, which include specific data on their <cite id=\"5\">50 educational projects</cite> and <cite id=\"6\">3 health clinics</cite> serving the Rohingya and other displaced communities."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2004</cite>, OBAT Helpers Inc. is a specialized humanitarian organization dedicated to serving displaced and marginalized communities in <cite id=\"2\">Bangladesh</cite>. The organization operates with a high degree of financial efficiency, maintaining a <cite id=\"3\">program expense ratio of 82.1%</cite> according to its most recent financial filings, while <cite id=\"4\">Charity Navigator reports a program expense ratio of 82.1%</cite> based on their specific evaluation criteria. OBAT Helpers focuses on breaking the cycle of poverty through a multi-sectoral approach that includes <cite id=\"5\">50 educational and training projects</cite> and <cite id=\"6\">3 health clinics</cite>. As a <cite id=\"7\">zakat-eligible organization</cite>, it provides a verified pathway for Muslim donors to support the <cite id=\"8\">fuqara (poor) and masakin (needy)</cite> within displaced populations. The charity's operations are characterized by strong governance, evidenced by a <cite id=\"9\">board of 22 members</cite> and a <cite id=\"10\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>. Despite a <cite id=\"11\">3-year revenue CAGR of -11.4%</cite>, the organization maintains <cite id=\"12\">5.7 months of working capital</cite>, ensuring operational resilience in challenging environments.",
